text:
i was battered and scattered,
i was frightened and scared,
with the fear of his touch everywhere,
i cry but shy away from saying,
i get blames on me of his wrong doings.

i tried to bury it,
cry and sleep over it,
but all in vain,
i cried every night time and again,
from a cheerful girl i became a meek mouse,
hiding from the eyes of lusty beasts everywhere.

i became prisoner of my own shame,
shuned in my own personal cage of blame ,
i could not leave like that any longer,
suffocating from everywhere for so so longer.

so i did what i had to do,
raised my voice and told the truth,
now that it was prime time,
with #metoo going stronger now, then ever.
.
-someone.
.

text:
collection: pop up poetry
#44 from a mother to her sons

poem 44 of 365. as part of the #fwwrinktober prompt series, @forwomenwhoroar asked for a work on 'me too'. like almost every women i know i have experienced unwanted advances, horrific words and insults, and unwanted physical touching. the conversations for me about the experience of sexual and physical violation in all its forms has made me resolute as a mother, that the best thing i can do for the #metoo movement is to help my son's understand body autonomy and agency and that every single person on the planet has this right over their own body.

by honouring their own bodies, and honouring the bodies of others, this is one way that they can honour me too. it is also one way that i can contribute to protecting others from the scourge of physical and sexual assault.

learn the art: poetry can be used to further discussions about important political and social topics. don't be scared to pick up a pen for a cause that you are passionate about.

text:
@sensusancollins 
it is your duty as a senator to listen to and represent your constituents. by confirming brett kavanaugh to the supreme court, you have largely failed your constituents, and therefore you have failed your job. in the past, you have voted against equal pay for women, you have voted to remove federal funding from sanctuary cities, you have voted to increase military spending, you have voted for a tax bill that essentially rips healthcare away from millions of people... and now, you are confirming a lying predator to the supreme court. time and time again, you have failed to listen to your constituents and to do your job. you should not be in office.

no matter your motives for confirming kavanaugh‚Äì you are harming women, survivors, and marginalized people everywhere and sending a message that we do not matter. it‚Äôs disgusting that you would confirm someone like kavanaugh to the supreme court just to maintain your proximal power from association with powerful white men.  it‚Äôs disgusting that you would confirm someone so terrible just for the sake of voting by party lines and furthering your political party. it‚Äôs disgusting that you would even dare to say that you believe that ford was assaulted and that the #metoo movement matters, yet you have the audacity to assert that ford was confused and you don‚Äôt believe that kavanaugh was the person who assaulted her (ford said she was 100% certain under oath; meanwhile, information is coming out of the woodwork that point out kavanaugh‚Äôs lies). you either believe and support survivors or you do not. we see you and we see through your lies; do not act like you support survivors while you do not believe us and instead empower predators.

you are on the wrong side of history; your actions are not dissimilar from those who supported slavery and those who opposed the civil rights movement. you are upholding rape culture. you are upholding white supremacy. and you are a downright liar for trying to pass as a moderate when you vote by party lines and ignore the concerns and wishes of your constituents.

you will be voted out of office. or just do us all a favor and leave now.

thanks for nothing.

text:
#metoo #metootz. monalisa ameangua kilio  ukumbini alipokuwa akizungumzia jinsi mabinti wanaotamani kuingia kwenye tasnia ya filamu wanavyonyanyaswa kingono sehemu wanazokwenda kuomba kusaidiwa.
.
monalisa aliangua kilio hicho ndani ya ukumbi wa makumbusho ya taifa, posta jijini dar ambapo alikuwa akizindua mpango wa kuwaendeleza mabinti wenye vipaji vya kuigiza uitwao monalisa act.
.
katika tukio hilo, mgeni rasmi alikuwa naibu waziri wa habari, sanaa utamaduni na michezo; juliana shonza ambapo kabla ya kutoa hotuba, monalisa alipanda jukwaani na kuanza kuelezea kilimchomsukuma kuanzisha mpango huo.
.
mona alisema kuwa anajua mabinti wengi wakienda kwa watu kuomba kusaidiwa ili waoneshe vipaji vyao, wengi huishia kudhalilishwa kingono ndipo wasaidiwe, jambo ambalo alililaani vikali. .
.
"ukweli mabinti wengi wana vipaji vya filamu lakini wanaishia kukata tamaa na vipaji vyao kupotea, hii ni kwa sababu wanapokwenda kuomba msaada wameishia kuombwa rushwa ya ngono, jambo ambalo siyo zuri kabisa,‚Äù alisema mona huku machozi yakimlengalenga na hata aliposhuka na kwenda kuwakumbatia baadhi ya mabinti alijikuta akilia.
@monalisatz

text:
y‚Äôall. we got death threats from some dude‚Äôs manga account today. what an exhausting couple of days. ü§¶üèº‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è major girl time and love needed. being a part of the opal club and being surrounded by amazing, kind, open-minded people has put me in a bubble of love and understanding. ‚Ä¢

deleting vile, disgusting, absolutely awful comments from our previous post about rape has become a full-time job. ‚Ä¢
‚Ä¢
someone asked us via dm why we are deleting these revolting trump-troll comments off our page, and isn‚Äôt it better to let everyone see how awful they are? one trump-troll got so offended that he sent us threats via dm. the thing is...there is enough of them with their foul language and horrid opinions out there. hey, i mean, one is in the white house as i write this! so you know what? i‚Äôm fucking deleting shit i don‚Äôt want on my page. i‚Äôm also genuinely confused about the fact that people spend their time going through a hashtag (i‚Äôm guessing the hashtags #stopkavanaugh #kavanaugh #metoo #brettkavanaugh #christineblaseyford and #abortion ?) and spending hours checking back and spewing shit on a post that spoke about statistics and rape survivors. it‚Äôs insane to me. ‚Ä¢
‚Ä¢
i just want to thank every single one of you who dmed us, dmed me personally, commented, emailed me. your love and support is so strong and beautiful. i am so grateful for you. thank you for being part of the opal club and growing with us. thank you for being patient as we develop and finding our footing. we are a tiny team and we are so young. our community is beautiful and loving because of you. our goal is to raise up voices, empower women, and be entirely genuine. thank you for being here. thank you for being so kind. üôåüèº @daphnaeremina

text:
we were in dlf mall of india yesterday and 70% of the men there were on their phones instead of staring women - and it was beautiful. i don't know whether it was because of the #metoo or the navratras but i think we should have more #metoo and celebrate navratras often solely for the men to take the percentage to 100. 
where: zizo, dlf mall of india
what: tomato basil soup and  dum chicken biryani

i haven't done these in a while now. i've previously reviewed many places which serve awesome biryani. this is a new addition and i'm all in for restaurants trying out something other than tradional biryanis.

soup: i love soups anyway !! i wanted to order their new shawarma soup which is a new edition to their menu but navratra and the madam did not want to upset goddess durga so i had to satisfy with tomato basil soup which was good but was not at all a replacement for the shawarma soup so i will rate it 7/10.

biryani: madam had a craving for biryani but navratras so wanted to satisfy her cravings with the veg biryani but thank god i could convince madam to order dum chicken biryani. but for the chicken biryani she put a condition that i will have to eat all the chicken pieces and she will just go with the rice to which i gladly agreed (why wouldn't i). so yes the dum. chicken biryani was pretty nice and different but not extra ordinary so here zizo will have to satisfy themselves with a 7/10. 
anyway, it was a great experience and i thanked the guy serving us for being such a nice host and tolerating with the madam's tantrums !! #tasty

.

text:
as i hear the denial and minimization
the "she's doing it for attention"
the "why so late?" the "she's opportunistic"
.
i wonder if deniers, minimizers,
upholders of unquestioned patriarchy
of all shapes, sizes, and genders...
will ever start with listening.
without disgust for women who speak up.
i may  be exhausted explaining myself,
but in the core of my being...
i always knew that the time for women...
was meant to come in my lifetime.
.
bring on the resistance.
no change ever happened without it.

text:
//
.
i stepped back from the door, one step at a time, and promised myself never to open that door again. with trembling hands i have put all my things inside that door, all those souvenirs that used to mean something to me. those precious moments of childhood, long gone. i have snitched the keys and hidden them away. and now, i laugh with you all and pretend that the door never existed. .
.
amidst all those sleepless nights, the door comes back to real every time. sometimes it starts pounding like the little heart in my chest and i don't know how to stop it again. .
.
it started with a pop up notification last night. my friend has confessed her #metoo story. and the little girl inside that door screamed with envy. i never know why i always let her down. why am i too weak to accept my flaws and search for the keys to open that door?
.
i know her anguish, her desperation towards me. cause i am stupid and haven't learned from my mistakes so far. i still blame myself, even those who are surrounded by me, but never that person who has caused everything. being helpless and tired, i raised my voice back at her because i am too afraid to raise my voice with her.
.
often i try to free her from that place but i am scared of the rotten memories that stink there.
-kalpana

text:
when i'd come to bombay in late 2016 to start a career in the hindi film industry. i started looking for jobs, one of them being with a director. i went to his apartment in versova and was told that the movie is about ' girls going wild'. hence, a series of sexual questions started, how do you behave when you're horny, what is your sexual fantasy, etc. he suggested i should enact the scene. i refused, being reluctant. he insisted, that i should enact being turned on. as i was hesitant, he took the opportunity to 'enact' the scene himself and, felt me up and groped my butt. i shoved him away and left the place and the city.

post this incident, in delhi, i received a call from mukesh chhabra casting company for an interview. i got the job and it has been the best opportunity, an industry outsider could get. a place where all my doubts and reservations regarding the film industry had drastically changed. i couldn't speak to him the first day i met him as i was too overwhelmed since he'd been a huge inspiration. he asked me to 'chill and carry on with work'. he built in me a kind of confidence that i could speak and hold meetings with any big shot in the industry without having any fear in mind. cctv cameras were installed in the office especially to cater to such allegations and, calls to females post 8:30 pm were made by female employees only. i had to leave the company on a bitter note after a year for my own personal reasons. yet, the experience i'd had there and how comfortable he'd  made all of us employees feel is always what i'd be thankful for.

today, in the wake of the #metoo movement, there have been sexual allegations raised against the man i deeply admire and have had a major influence in changing my perspective about the industry. this is my personal experience of working at mccc and with mr. mukesh chhabra.

i support the #metoo movement. i don't know what the truth is and it will come out when it has to. having said that, let's, also, not trivialise this important issue by misusing the platform, so that the focus on the greater good of this cause remains.

#truthwillalwaysprevail @castingchhabra @mukeshchhabracc

when i'd come to bombay in late 2016 to start a career in the hindi film industry. i started looking for jobs, one of them being with a director. i went to his apartment in versova and was told that the movie is about ' girls going wild'. hence, a series of sexual questions started, how do you behave when you are horny, what is your sexual fantasy, etc. he suggested i should enact the scene. i refused, being reluctant. he insisted, that i should enact being turned on. as i was hesitant, he took the opportunity to 'enact' the scene himself and, felt me up and groped my butt. i shoved him away and left the place and the city.

post this incident, in delhi, i received a call from mukesh chhabra casting company for an interview. i got the job and it has been the best opportunity, an industry outsider could get. a place where all my doubts and reservations regarding the film industry had drastically changed. i couldn't speak to him the first day i met him as i was too overwhelmed since he'd been a huge inspiration. he asked me to 'chill and carry on with work'. he built in me a kind of confidence that i could speak and hold meetings with any big shot in the industry without having any fear in mind. cctv cameras were installed in the office especially to cater to such allegations and, calls to females post 8:30 pm were made by female employees only. i had to leave the company on a bitter note after a year for my own personal reasons. yet, the experience i'd had there and how comfortable he'd  made all of us employees feel is always what i'd be thankful for.

today, in the wake of the #metoo movement, there have been sexual allegations raised against the man i deeply admire and have had a major influence in changing my perspective about the industry. this is my personal experience of working at mccc and with mr. mukesh chhabra.

i support the #metoo movement. i do not know what the truth is and it will come out when it has to. having said that, let's, also, not trivialise this important issue by misusing the platform, so that the focus on the greater good of this cause remains.

text:
whatever is too small for you, that is.‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
people, jobs, careers, the story you tell yourself about who you are and how it is.‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
see, the universe wants us to keep growing into the larger story that's waiting for us, the one we're here to live.‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
and all the awful, bad, horrible, yucky stuff that happens along the way is meant, in part, to help strengthen our soul (i didn't make up the rules).‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
if you're sensitive, and/or introverted, and/or a survivor, and/or a scared li'l bunny (i am, or have been, all of them) ... trust me.‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
there's a much bigger story waiting for you, along with people who can see and respect and support and love you, and a great career in which you can make good money doing what you love.‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
all sorts of magic and mystery and adventure is resting in the treasure chest laying at the feet of the dragon.‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
you, too, can learn how to walk with the fear, toward the dragon.‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
for me, the stories of incest victim and childhood sexual assault survivor weren't big enough to hold all of who i am.‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
it took years, millions of mistakes and wrong turns, plenty of "no, i can't; it's too hard."‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
but i persevered, stuck with it, explored and experimented with all sorts of cool things. i learned how to step into and start living the larger, grand narrative of my life.‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
which has become one of living richly, exploring deeply, and making space for all that is in this great, wondrous. and yes, sometimes absolutely horrific world.‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
let's do this!‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä

mark 10:17-30

17and as he was setting out on his journey, a man ran up and knelt before him, and asked him, "good teacher, what must i do to inherit eternal life?"18and jesus said to him, "why do you call me good? no one is good but god alone.19you know the commandments: `do not kill, do not commit adultery, do not steal, do not bear false witness, do not defraud, honor your father and mother.'"¬†20and he said to him, "teacher, all these i have observed from my youth."¬†21and jesus looking upon him loved him, and said to him, "you lack one thing; go, sell what you have, and give to the poor, and you will have treasure in heaven; and come, follow me."¬†22at that saying his countenance fell, and he went away sorrowful; for he had great possessions.¬†23and jesus looked around and said to his disciples, "how hard it will be for those who have riches to enter the kingdom of god!"¬†24and the disciples were amazed at his words. but jesus said to them again, "children, how hard it is to enter the kingdom of god!¬†25it is easier for a camel to go through the eye of a needle than for a rich man to enter the kingdom of god."26and they were exceedingly astonished, and said to him, "then who can be saved?"27jesus looked at them and said, "with men it is impossible, but not with god; for all things are possible with god."28peter began to say to him, "lo, we have left everything and followed you."¬†29jesus said, "truly, i say to you, there is no one who has left house or brothers or sisters or mother or father or children or lands, for my sake and for the gospel,¬†30who will not receive a hundredfold now in this time, houses and brothers and sisters and mothers and children and lands, with persecutions, and in the age to come eternal life.

text:
i was inspired to create a piece for my showing at @riverseagalleryastoria tonight in honor of the greek goddess, artemis. diana, her roman equivalent, is the daughter of zeus and leto, twin sister of apollo. she is the goddess of the moon, queen of the mountains, forests and hunting.  artemis is immortal and very powerful.  her powers include perfect aim with the bow and arrow, the ability to turn herself and others into animals, healing, disease, and control of nature.  she‚Äôs the goddess of childbirth, and the protector of small children, animals and the innocent.  she protected young girls from assault or unwanted male attention until until they were married.  she was beautiful and although she had many interested suiters, she maintained her virginity.  she asked her father to promise never to force her to marry, and therefore is known as the goddess of freedom.  she is depicted by the crescent moon, bow and arrow, three pillars and blue sky.  dogs, bear and deer were particularly important animals to artemis and she‚Äôs often depicted with them by her side. her stones are diamond, moonstone, pearl, crystal, iron and turquoise.  she is the inspiration for dc comic‚Äôs character, wonder woman.  in short, she is amazing and i felt called to conjure her energy at this very strange and debilitating time for women.

i was inspired to create a piece for my showing at @riverseagalleryastoria tonight in honor of the greek goddess, artemis. diana, her roman equivalent, is the daughter of zeus and leto, twin sister of apollo. she is the goddess of the moon, queen of the mountains, forests and hunting.  artemis is immortal and very powerful.  her powers include perfect aim with the bow and arrow, the ability to turn herself and others into animals, healing, disease, and control of nature.  she‚Äôs the goddess of childbirth, and the protector of small children, animals and the innocent.  she protected young girls from assault or unwanted male attention until until they were married.  she was beautiful and although she had many interested suiters, she maintained her virginity.  she asked her father to promise never to force her to marry, and therefore is known as the goddess of freedom.  she is depicted by the crescent moon, bow and arrow, three pillars and blue sky.  dogs, bear and deer were particularly important animals to artemis and she‚Äôs often depicted with them by her side. her stones are diamond, moonstone, pearl, crystal, iron and turquoise.  she is the inspiration for dc comic‚Äôs character, wonder woman.  in short, she is amazing and i felt called to conjure her energy at this very strange and debilitating time for women.

text:
#cruel 
today's inktober is different and it wasn't planned to be so.

yesterday was like any other normal day until i happened to see these angry posts against many very "respected" celebrities. curious, i read a bit more. what i discovered was a violent storm of stories of exploitation, destruction and trauma. 
the very fact that such a large majority of the population has experienced sexual abuse disturbs me. it isn't a matter of gender. it's about being a human and choosing not to. it's about giving respect, and deserving that.

#metoo

#inktober #inktober2018
#ink #artistsoninstagran

the manual includes information about:

text:
the last couple of days had me in a shitty place. the kind of sick news that has been surfacing around sexual abuse, had my heart broken, trust demolished and getting out of bed required will power. the stories of the #metoo movement in india and the graphic accounts of abuse and oppression that has come to light has left me incapacitated. chintan ruparel, the co-founder of ttt, allegedly the blue eyed boy was one of the writers i looked upto because of his effortless way with words and the way he conveyed simple everyday emotions, it moved me. his words were stellar, he on the other hand was full of shit. the accounts of him meeting with teens and college girls attending his writing workshop with big dreams, aspirations to be a writer and his flagrant misuse of power by gaslighting, egging and forcing himself, behaving in animalistic ways had left me completely shocked. 
enjoy the art, not the artist is a common tell, but i cannot see the beauty in the art if the artist is a sick fuck. what‚Äôs even astonishing is the ignorance of nut jobs who are victim shaming saying that the girls came to the hotel or that they consented to share a cab ride. use your brains, people. these sexual predators gain the trust of girls, they chat with them, make a show of how special they are, that is their modus operandi. they come to you in false pretexts of friendship and social drinking, behaving lovely and coy. is a woman not allowed to socialize, go out or have a drink? right there is the problem with this bigoted society. why are rules different for men and women? kissing forcibly/suddenly without consent is wrong you shit bags. but hey, marital rape is not a criminal offense in india, so i get why many of you don‚Äôt understand the concept of consent. 
of course these girls were frozen and cornered, and caught off guard. before they could muster courage to scream or escape, he bullied them into surrender. can you imagine being silenced like that? #metoo movement is the need of the hour. we need it in india, welcome it. share your stories. be bold for those who cannot find the strength in them. be a messenger for change. (cont'd in comments)

text:
a short little string of idea about waitressing with pictures from inside an abandoned bus up in the mountains . . .  after a long day of waiting tables yesterday and another one today, it‚Äôs funny how my mood affects my job. the happier i am, the more i smile, the more people (especially guys) feel like they are allowed to touch me. they grab my arm when i walk by to look at my tattoos, they rub their hand on my back when they say goodbye, they force a big, long hug despite the fact that i don‚Äôt even know their name. it‚Äôs crazy how many men mistake my optimistic outlook on life as a flirtatious endeavor towards them. i sometimes feel cautious about who i should be kind to, knowing very well they take this as an advance and then put me in the awkward position of turning down their requests to get lunch, go hiking whatever. it‚Äôs as if, because i do my job and i do it well, they feel entitled to my food service but also a little piece of me; they pay for a few moments of intimacy where money, which pays for what i need most (food and water, heat in my home, the necessities of living), is on the line. these people are my income, my paychecks are often $0-$10. without their tips, without the emotional exhaustion, i don‚Äôt have a wages. interesting. .
..

....
...
..

text:
this is not the story of a girl who was molested by five different men in a small lifetime of twenty one years.
this is not the story of the girl who was either too small to understand what was happening or too dumbfounded to react instantly.
this is not the story of the girl who kept her mouth shut even after everything because she was trying to avoid the blames of wearing short clothes, or drinking in a pub or being too friendly with someone.
this is not the story of the girl who couldn't gather enough courage to speak up against her molester.
this is not the story of the girl who had to relive her trauma day after day because she sees her molester everytime she steps out of her own house.
this is not the story of the girl who was scarred for life when she was only six years old.
because this is not the story of one single girl.
this is the story of every girl who had to face any type of harassment in their lives.
this is the story of every single girl who feels unsafe wherever she goes.
this is the story which warns all those men  who made girls uncomfortable, molested her, harassed her in any way.
it's high time you back down because a woman's fury has no bounds when it's out in the open after being bottled up for so long.
she is the incarnation of the goddesses and will burn you if you even put a finger on her now.
so back off.
your sorry won't lessen the pain which we have received for centuries due to the patriarch society but it can still be a small step in the direction of huge reforms.
and to all the women out there, who had the courage to speak up, i can't thank you enough.
because of your courage, many more were inspired to come out with their stories, to lessen a bit of baggage they have been carrying around for years.
my heart goes out for you and your family.
kudos to you and your courage.

#metoo #poetryfeels #words #writer #stories  #writerscommunity #poetrycommunity

in the light of allegations levied on @castingchhabra, i want to share my experience with him and within the organization.
i have been associated with him for last one year as i was his da on his film; from reading sessions to the edit table, i have a microscopic perception of his activities. i have never seen him misbehaving with any female, leave alone molesting or approaching someone with wrong intention. 
being an ace casting director, he would frequently be approached by aspiring actresses but he always maintained his professional territory and would divert them to talk to me for any casting related queries. i have seen him standing selflessly by new comers and giving the talent opportunity. i have a lot of female friends in the acting/casting diaspora who share the same opinion about him. mccc has the safest environment for female actresses, i can personally vouch for the professional integrity maintained in our office premises.
truth shall prevail!

text:
it starts with how we learn our gender roles- a social construction of what it ‚Äúmeans‚Äù to be a boy or girl and then a man or woman. we learn these roles from the portrayals in media, which are sometimes reenforced and sometimes contradicted in real life.
-
at some point for girls, ‚Äúcute‚Äù becomes ‚Äúsexy,‚Äù and we as young women try to navigate the elusive space designated for female sexuality. as a female, we deal with a #catch22, cautioned not be too sexy as to ‚Äúinvite‚Äù unwanted attention, while being under heavy pressure to fit certain beauty ideals.
-
men are taught to be aggressive and physical, women are taught to be pretty and gentle. this combination is worsened by the lack of #healthyrelationships and #sexualconsent #education.
-
the media sexualizes violence, and the majority of mainstream porn features physical and verbal aggression with the female showing a neutral or positive reaction. welcome to #rapeculture. for more information, contact me for a training.

text: most days this month i have wanted to run in the opposite direction of my calling. last year when i started my therapy practice i had no idea the #metoo movement would come along and i‚Äôd be doing some heavy lifting as a trauma therapist while at the same time being forced face to face with all of the times the sanctity of my own body and my sacred sexual energy have been disrespected, demeaned, objectified, manipulated and taken without my consent. i hold so many stories of sexual violence that i bear witness to everyday- the cruelty, the devastation, the shattered broken dreams, the rage that arises from the realization that there will never be justice. we have had things taken from us that there is no way to repay. and i get to watch people heal, to let themselves shatter and then put themselves back together again. sometimes it feels like we‚Äôre holding ourselves together with duck tape and a glue stick. but i have seen with my own eyes the possibility of healing, of claiming our power after it‚Äôs been ripped from us, of finding a way to get our dreams even while the perpetrators of violence live on unscathed. i hold in my body lifetimes worth of anger for all of the women who have come before me who have put up with rape and second class citizenship as par for the course. these last weeks i have broken spells of silence, i have gone back and reclaimed my nos, i have spoken the words that never made it out of my mouth because i was scared or frozen, i have asked for justice from those who have taken from me. and still there‚Äôs so much that will never be fixed. so many times that a man‚Äôs desire trumped his ability to see me as my own subjective human and not an object for his own pleasure. so many times a man‚Äôs misled belief that he‚Äôs entitled to my sexuality, my femininity, my kindness, my attention has been pushed onto me in ways i wasn‚Äôt prepared to defend myself from. there are so many apologies owed to me that i will never receive. speaking these truths and claiming our anger is the pathway to reconnecting w our power. it‚Äôs painful, hard work. be loving, patient and generous towards yourself and all the women, femmes and survivors in your life right now‚ô•Ô∏è‚ô• ‚ô•

text: #worldmentalhealthday it makes me incredibly sad to think about all of the people suffering in silence in fear that if they tell someone they are struggling with depression or anxiety, they are crazy or week or even pretending. i‚Äôve always believed people when they were courageous enough to tell me they were struggling. ten years ago, i couldn‚Äôt relate but always had a deep compassion for them. today, i can relate! i have had a traumatic few years and suddenly i noticed this unfamiliar feeling i just couldn‚Äôt shake. at first i thought i had a stomach issues, then i thought i was super hungry so, i ate. then i started feeling like i was struggling to breath and thought it was my heart. i‚Äôm kind of self diagnosed right now because i haven‚Äôt had time to seek professional help but, i figured out i have some form of ptsd which causes anxiety in varying degrees. this is even harder to share because as a christian, you are looked at as having little or no faith and that‚Äôs why you‚Äôre going through this. or, people think you‚Äôre seeking attention. the unfortunate thing is when people are labeled this way, they don‚Äôt talk about it. the end result of that for so many hasn‚Äôt been good. i encourage anyone else who is struggling to say ‚Äúme too!‚Äù i‚Äôm suffering and i need help. if you‚Äôre a christian, this doesn‚Äôt change who god is, it reveals more of who he is because none of us are perfect and that‚Äôs exactly why we need him more and more each day. he‚Äôs a good, good father! üôè‚ù§Ô∏è that will never change no matter what we are going through #metoo

text:
‚Äúyou are a feisty feminist‚Äù, they would say.
and you would rightly presume so,
for you believed in equality, liberation and the need to voice your rights.

until that day,
in the hotel room far away from your city,
you were ambushed, touched and felt, while being told how pretty you are.
your otherwise messy hair turned into ‚Äòperfect curls beautifully resting on the swell of your breast.‚Äô
and while being coerced to quaff alcohol down your throat, you heard a whisper that said ‚Äò later in the night, you‚Äôll be driven up the wall.‚Äô you were there, present in that very situation
being harassed, being hassled,
and yet you could barely fathom that perhaps you were.
the obvious instincts were supposed to kick in, the strength to fight should have come but you froze like a statue, oblivious to the abuse,
and the only thing that lingered (still does) until your last breath is the regret of not acting.
-
i wish this never befalls on you.
i wish you stop looking for a knight and look for a sword instead.
i wish you find it lying within you.
and i wish you use it to protect yourself.

i hope you remember that you are a weapon. 
remember to keep yourself loaded.
and most importantly, remember,
silence is not the rent you pay to exist in the world as a woman.

text:
an open letter to parents

dear,
parents of a hosteller girl,

okay, society is devastating. it might not be fit for her. but why always she should adjust. tell your daughter to fight back all odds. i know you are afraid when she is  alone at late night. but it's not her fault that she is raped. it's those lecherous eyes staring at her boobs. it's okay, she won't be late, won't be raped as you won't allow her to fly. you have clipped the wings, before she even tried. 
don't worry mom and dad. you have given birth to a fighter, a 'daughter' no less than a son.
she knows how to fight back. 
just make her bold, but before that, be bolder.

yours 
hosteller daughter..
nandita jha

text:
beautiful comments from a writer geetanjali arora on #metoo 
you do me favors, i do you favors 30 years later lets call it *"me too"*... a strong woman does not wait 30, 20, 10 years to speak up, she slaps him on the first *"bad touch"* and knocks him out... don't hide your weakness, the favors in returns that you enjoyed and the work you got by *"i was too scared"* cry now... you were scared to say no then because it was hard to stand up for what was right and you were scared to loose your status and position in the work place, so *you chose* to accept the molestation and went back for more... its very easy to play the *abla nari* card later and gain sympathy... *the shakti does not wait for a later date to speak up, she silences the evil on the spot...* my thoughts on this nonsense of *'me too'*... i don't have *'me too'* stories, anyone who tried got a tight slap then and there and i was never afraid to walk out with my head held high - be it in a job or relationship!!! "strong women don't have *'me too'* sob stories, they only have - *i slapped him back*  short essays"

text:
i have been an online fitness coach for damn near 2 years and have loved every minute of it. i have passion for what i do, helping others, the company i get to work with and the community that it has. .
in the last 2 years i have grown so much it is incredible! i‚Äôm not even going to talk about my weight loss journey (because you already know that story, if not go scroll my page for a minute), i am talking mental growth, self worth and confidence. i am not the same person i was 2 years ago. i don‚Äôt have the same relationships i had 2 years ago. .
first i learned i needed to love myself then i evaluated all of my relationships and if there wasn‚Äôt a two way highway and a push in both directions to be the best person you can be on both ends i cut my losses. either they weren‚Äôt healthy for me or i wasn‚Äôt healthy for them. and i didn‚Äôt feel bad about it and won‚Äôt apologize for it. .
lots of growth and lots of passion. but i still felt like something was missing. i needed more drive something i could really have a voice in. nothing political, that‚Äôs not my thing at all! and then lots of recent events have happened. here in iowa we‚Äôve had women kidnapped and killed, a woman here in my town was murdered in broad daylight on a golf course, all of this #metoo movement and supporting each other (this is not open for debate, please notice my wording‚Ä¶ supporting each other). .
i have never engaged in social media arguments and debates until a few weeks ago. you bet your ass i have been in many of those. some didn‚Äôt end with any resolutions, some ended in mutual understanding, some ended in making new friends (weird how that works when we support each other!).
.
on wednesday a friend of mine and i were talking about all of this and i had an ah-ha moment. and immediately dropped my plans, ran home, did some research, signed up for a training and bam! new project under way. i am still coaching, i will always coach. this new project is intertwined with that but is so much more to me. .
i know this post is super long but i am so very excited to almost announce what this project is and how it is going to change so much for so many! .
official announcement: next week <3

text:
discovering upper limits of your physical power doesn‚Äôt always feel great. it certainly isn‚Äôt nice, in the sense that ‚Äúniceness‚Äù is about making everyone around you comfortable.
.
grow into your rage, and you will drip sweat and tears. it won‚Äôt be pretty. you‚Äôll make sounds. you won‚Äôt look like a good girl. you might get winded, gassed, sometimes nauseous from the exertion. ü§¢muscles burn and fatigue. you may tap into the ocean of grief and sadness that‚Äôs just underneath rage like miles of earth and rock. lifetimes of it stored, maybe.
.
but, beloved, this is both true and true: üåü the discomfort of feeling one‚Äôs strength is so much better than the feeling of powerlessness, of helplessness. üåü you rise up with a roar instead of a whimper.
.
the way you do this is up to you. experience your physical power your way: perhaps in strong, sturdy legs as you dance; in deadlifts and burpees; in hearty strides of a long run; in the way you‚Äôre magically nursing life into your baby with just your breasts and arms.
.
my favorite is to feel the explosive feedback of letting my upper body loose and wild into a punching bag, where i can literally see and hear the impact. many women who join me say they‚Äôve never punched anything, ever, not at all. and they discover they love it. üí•üëäüèªüí•
.
if you‚Äôd like to join, i‚Äôm hosting another sister circle/rage room. it‚Äôs free. i promise to hold a steady container that is safe, sacred, and respectful. you will also feel the upper limits of your power.
.
last time a participant was surprised by the vacuum she created by letting loose. she said it felt like something had emptied out inside of her and there was now a space that she could choose to fill however she liked, with love, and kindness.
.
that‚Äôs exactly what it‚Äôs about. exactly, that.
.
tap into your physical power. join us for our second sister circle/rage room saturday october 20 at 6pm at @rocksolidkm in little falls. dm or text me for more info. .
#rageon #metoo #riseup #kalima #montclair #anger #sacredpower #chaninicholas #ownit #feelit

text: as a feminist i quite often get asked my response to certain controversial media revelations, particularly the recent uprising of men in power facing sexual allegations against numerous women. recently, i‚Äôve been asked a few times about the brett kavanaugh case. i know who he is and i‚Äôve heard the allegations, but i‚Äôve not been following it. as a feminist, i‚Äôve not been following the brett kavanaugh case. ‚Äòmake women visible.‚Äô i am tired of brave women coming forward and being silenced. you are not the problem. i‚Äôm tired of men failing to accept and take accountability for their actions, i‚Äôm tired. women have been shamed and their allegations have been branded false, when they find the courage to speak out and say #metoo women have been hushed. i‚Äôm not following the kavanaugh plot because i‚Äôm sick of reading stories where women aren‚Äôt believed. sick of reading articles where the perpetrators, the men, are shown in a better light than the victim. i‚Äôm tired of reading articles based on the true events, incorporating manipulated facts in order to encourage the systematic oppression of women and their stories.

text:
truth is... this is my truth... my reality here and now... i am beat down... i am broken... and i am tired. there are only so many times i can try and lie to myself and try to feel happy... paint on a fake smile to hide all of my pain... i'm embaressed...
despite feeling like i knew what to do to help myself... i am lost...
despite trying to fight to move forward... i am still here.... i know it will take time... i am told it will take time... but who has time.... life doesn't ever stop... how to heal and process the past, when the present gives you more and more and we must move on? i ran to the edge of earth to find stillness and process what has been, i begged for time to heal and guidance... only to have more set on my shoulders... i do not understand.... i have and am begging for help... from anyone who can see or hear me... god?.... i  feel so hopeless and tired.

yet on farms, where pigs are kept in row after row after row of gestation crates throughout their pregnancies, they're also among the most abused. the 2-foot-wide cages are so narrow, the animals cannot even¬†turn around. they chew on the bars,¬†wave their heads incessantly back and forth,¬†or lie on the pavement in an apparent state of dejection. nearly immobilized, the pigs spend months staring ahead, waiting to be fed, likely going out of their minds.

_

i get the idea that this retrograde has to do with sexual healing... i have been having a lot of fast-forwarding flashes of the past that seem to be flying out of my energy field... like i don‚Äôt need these surface scars anymore... perhaps a test...
üï≥
to see if i can handle what‚Äôs next... which has opened some quick glimpses of things that i was not aware of... from my childhood... answers and pieces are starting to come to me... and yet i feel that it‚Äôs still just the surface...
‚úèÔ∏è
it is my intention to finally let these inner feelings and traumas come to the surface now... that i am finally at a place that i heal from the knowing...
üí°
i have a bad memory... even short term... but more so i have large gaps of memories or pieces ...of memories that can not be seen by my conscious mind... they are black...
üôè
i have beat myself up for 42 years because i can not remember the depth of my sexual trauma... i can‚Äôt recall all the scenes... and the not knowing really fucked me up in my twenties... how could i feel and know this thing and have no proof?!
üå±
regardless whether i regain those memories... i accept any opportunity for my soul... body and mind to heal itself... i will no longer stand in the way...

girls from as young as five may be dedicated to the goddess. dedicating girls as 'joginis' has been illegal since 1988, but the practice continues. in 2015 the jogini commission estimated that there are 80,000 'joginis' in the states of telangana and andhra pradesh. almost all 'joginis' are dalits.

extreme poverty, traditional beliefs and superstitions are major factors in the decision to dedicate. the girls rarely realise what will happen to them, but since becoming a 'jogini' is believed to bring good fortune to the community, the family and even the girl herself, the pressure to dedicate is immense.

how many times have you stood up against sexual misconduct ?
aren't we also the contributers towards making this society the way it is ? have we ever stopped our friends when women are seen as objects?
or are we too a part of it ?
it's time we take responsibility, redefine the society and provide our support to this long awaited movement.

text:
today is a wonderful day to check in with yourself and inquire about your beliefs! what are they?  where did they come from? do they actually belong to you or did you learn them from your wobbly past? .
sometimes we live in the background of what we actually believe is true.  we hide out of fear of living our deepest authenticity.  the question is:  do the beliefs of others have to be true for you?
.
thinking is good for you.  critical thinking‚Äî-even better! resist following the trends.  whether it is fashion, food, word tends, political (!) trends, question all of it. my answers always lead me to more questions thus i am never board!

text:
‚Ä¢¬∞come, let's play a game called i always win.¬∞‚Ä¢ they saw that it was wrong and yet they kept quiet and didn't do anything. they low-key told you to speak up against your ill treatment. . which you didn't. instead you wrote down a list of what could go wrong, weighed your options and realized that a lot was at stake. so at night, you accepted their invitation and 'went up into the room.' silently, they watched you go in from a distance and their hearts sank, because they too went up into that room once. they knew what happens up there and yet the idea of what could happen if they didn't go up scared them the most. 
silence is deafening, isn't it? but at some point you realise that some things are better left not said and buried behind in the past than fighting for what is right. that can take time and its draining. 
after all was said and done, you pulled yourself together, walked out the room and slipped it all under the carpet, like how everyone else did in the past. you hoped that after a while it wouldn't hurt no more, but you were wrong. . it haunts you everyday, especially when another person says #metoo. 
sadly, the bully always wins and sometimes the bullied becomes the bully to protect themselves from getting bullied ever again. #iwritewhatilike #thepuppyepisodesüíë

text:
at a certain point, we have to stop blaming everyone and everything else, and take responsibility for ourselves.

we may have been programmed by our parents, teachers, community, colonization and outside world, but we can and must, take sovereignty of ourselves. of our mind, our words, our actions.

we are not victims.

to anything.

let us take our divine power.

and similarly, stop making excuses for others, as though they are all powerless to their surroundings too. ‚Äúoh he had such a poor childhood. that‚Äôs why he beat, or calls names, or raped‚Äù. fuck our programming. and fuck the programming of everyone else.

what we have right now, is the present.

and in the present, i am not a victim. i choose my thoughts. i choose my words. i choose my actions.

in order to shift into the new energy, we must be willing to let go of the old.

those who rape, hit, beat, or abuse, you have no excuse. 
those who stay silent or allow it, you have no excuse.

all we have is right now. delete our old programming. it isn‚Äôt helping us, it‚Äôs harming us.

truth heals.

rise.

text:
sisters, we are there for you. don't feel alone. as a community, we will guide you towards light
‚ñ™Ô∏è‚ñ™Ô∏è
there's this gnawing hollowness in my heart, ever since i've been reading stories, confessions and articles of brave, brave girls coming out, and sharing their experiences.
.
i can only imagine how much courage it must take, and i am there for all of you.
.
most of these stories are just painful- they were forced, harassed, and had no other choice. i wish i could say- i understand - but i know i can't. no girl who hasn't been in that position can understand. all i can say is- i am there for you.
.
on the flipside, i have been reading stories about toxic relationships, and infatuations where it was consensual. the guy is wrong there too, i understand. but, is he only wrong?
.
i don't know, they trouble me even more. i don't know who to blame. is the guy a 'rapist' in such a case? i agree he might be a womaniser, and that's sick.
.
don't lash out at me, please. i am just like you, deeply upset by everything. i am just like you, thinking about what's wrong and what's right. and i want to understand it better, to reach out and help those who need.
‚ñ™Ô∏è‚ñ™Ô∏è‚ñ™Ô∏è
#metoo #metoomovement #mentalhealth #mentalhealthawareness #life #courage #strength #iamthereforyou #stayunited  #believewomen #believesurvivors #crime

text:
they said it was impossible. 
we said: watch us! 
and then we created the new academy and a prize in literature that is unique in so many ways. 
we have no fundings and founding fathers. 
we have no kings in our back or crowns in our pockets. 
but we have our passion and our vision. 
and we stand up for democracy, equality and diversity. 
we include the world by asking them to vote for their favourite authors, nominated by librarians. our expert jury finally chose the winner: maryse conde. we announced her name yesterday at a beautiful event at the public library. 
250 persons and media from hong kong to spain attended. people from around the globe followed our live-stream. you can see the event on you tube. 
the news reached every corner of the world. people praised our collective efforts, capacity and creativity. 
we're proud to live by example. to practice what others preach. to protest against privileged patriarchal and misogynist structures that belong to the past by creating something new. there are alternative ways than their highway. we can and must change what we cannot accept. together. 
so thank you all for your support. thanks to the heroic members of the new academy, most of them women, but also some men. skilled, talented, professional persons that sacrifice their precious time to make a difference. 
thanks to the librarians, the jury, the voters, the readers, the literature lovers and all of you that share our visions and help us make this dream come true. 
next stop is the gala ceremony the 9th of december at berns. until then we need money for the prize. contribute through our kick-starter or swish www.thenewacademy.se
here are some pics. i will also share articles from the guardian to new york times and el pais and le monde. @dennyaakademien2018 #vision #timesup #metoo #thenewacademy2018 #library #award #stockholm #wecandoittogether #whentheygolow

the cab i booked was waiting at the end of the street and i walked upto it in this dress crossing the back lane of the market.
from the moment i stepped out of the house till i stepped in the cab, i was assured  by the all those eyes following me, that i feel my best at being awkwardly attractive. 
i held my clutch tight to my upper body and walked as close to the parked cars and dark tress as i could. to protect the purse, ofcourse.

this is just a day, everyday.
i always hold my bag tight to protect it.
and myself.
so far, so good. 
#metoo #safeandsound

text: i know when i‚Äôm emotionally triggered i‚Äôm not in the present moment. if on autopilot my body goes into past trauma to a state of wound re-enactment. this causes me to be clouded by my pain falling into the victim role which prevents me from consciously choosing to perceive the best outcome in how i want to show up as my truest and highest expression of myself that not only benefits me but to others. i no longer allow anyone including myself to rob me for feeling anything less than, disempowering myself. i choose to not allow what others say or do negatively impact me anymore. instead i keep my heart open, to raise my vibrations and expand my consciousness in how i want to feel: empowered from the place of peace. inner #peace is not absence of chaos in life, but the ability to align from within in how i want to feel - that boat i envision myself as and respond from that space, the home frequency i‚Äôve been memorising myself to feel: calm and steady with composure - the equanimity riding out any waves life presents to me with grace, compassion, unbothered, still and aware observing where actually nothing has to be figured out by the intellect. when i‚Äôm in love with me, how others react and think don‚Äôt determine how i feel about myself. cuz shallowness doesn‚Äôt demand depth&substance; it‚Äôs the manifestation from a disempowered belief where people aren‚Äôt being fully present, not engaging in #real #connection #transparency and #vulnerability . those who choose to hide in a fake world, hiding behind fake names and numbers trying to claim that you know me getting information from others to find my whereabouts, contact details, etc - you‚Äôre commiting a crime. stalking. harassing.  #metoo did you know 1 out of 5 women have had experienced sexual abuse? if it‚Äôs any form of abuse, the ratio now becomes? remember we all have a female figure in our lives: #mother #sister #daughter #niece #girlfriend #bff #wife #aunt #teacher #doctor or pet etc. the world needs to change the narrative in how we treat our women by starting with ourselves creating opportunities to live in the new energy of the reality we all are creating. #iamlove #love #speakthetruth #nojudgement #noprejudice

text:
child  abuse is indeed a silent epidemic. 
1 in 3 girls and 1 in 6 boys are abused before age 18. 90% of predators are family members, friends of the family, domestic staff, teachers, coach etc. they are well-known & trusted by you and i.

at this free event, you will learn: - the dynamics of child abuse
- signs and effects of child abuse
- how to identify an abuser
- proven strategies for prevention
- effects of domestic violence on  children. - you will also hear real life stories from survivors.
-have access to educative materials -the first 50 people will get a book titled - "unspoken family secrets written by christianah akindolie, a renowned child safety advocate.

this event is for parents, women groups, religious leaders, teachers, survivors, youth leaders etc

over a 100 people have registered already. we need a 100 more. seats are fast filling up!

to register, send a whatsapp message "i want to attend" to 08166655527 or 08027835885.

text:
#metoo movement started in oct'17 and since then voices against sexual harassment has been rising and getting strong. a society where freedom is gender specific and voices needing our support are neglected is not an acceptable society anymore. we should unite, take responsibility and fulfill our part.
how many times have you stood up against sexual misconduct ?
aren't we also the contributers towards making this society the way it is ? have we ever stopped our friends when women are seen as objects?
or are we too a part of it ?
it's time we take responsibility, redefine the society and provide our support to this long awaited movement.

text: performing a new show for the first time in front of an audience is always both exciting and stressful. especially this show. i have never worked on and performed something so experimental and creative like "carnival of souls: neon animation with live action". it is not only a one woman show, it is also very different and new. the never been done before ever in the world kinda thing. after weeks of rehearsals in the dark with no one but @jack.feldstein - who wrote the script, neon animated the film and directed the piece - to see it, look at it and comment on it, it was so extremely special and beautiful to perform it in front of an audience late last night at dixon place. what a great day it was! not only the performance itself, but the whole day including tech rehearsal when we found out the beauty of the possibilities we had at @dixonplace. what an amazing theater. i want to thank dixon place and i want to thank you, the very special audience who saw our new, strange and experimental piece for the first time. thank you to all of you who were there: @paulocoelhomusic, @jac.grady, barbara, richard, @thirsavantil, and more. thank you very very much for your support! ‚ù§Ô∏è

text:
kangana lashes out against those belittling #metoo & calls for the uniting of the movement 
kangana is a fighter, and we all are aware of it. recently kangana was asked about the latest vikas bahl controversy and the allegations his ex-wife has levelled on her, she said "women should not stand against each other. this is the time to support each other and fight against the people who harass them. ofcourse, vikas's wife will have a different experience. being an ex wife his social behavior may not be known to her that well, the equation has changed so may be her experience is different, shall we settle at that? like i said, the harasser and the victims who have shared their harassment are different from my experience, this maybe the case but i am not saying that the other person is wrong or richa is wrong. everybody can have a different experience. not every individual is the same with everyone. sometimes the behavior also changes according to the situation. so may be her experience is different so me saying that she is wrong or i am right will be totally inappropriate. but the bottom line is that we need to make this place secure and all that is happening is good, that the moment allegations are being raised people are taking away work from them, otherwise these people are shameless otherwise they will never be ashamed of what they are doing. " 
kangana further praised aamir khan and akshay kumar by saying, "i'm impressed with their decision of not working with people who have allegations of harassment , otherwise this will just become a shallow talk.  there should have been something concrete coming out and what is concrete is that taking power away from these people will only lead to betterment without power who will these people then harrass. then no one will get harassed." when asked about sajid khan and alok nath's name also being dragged in this kangana said, well i don't know them personally and it's high time that women don't get questioned for raising their voice. women have been questioned for way too long.  #kanganaranaut
name: Viral Bhayani

text:
'why didn't she say anything?'
'why didn't she report?' i keep coming across these questions so many times that i really feel it needs to be addressed especially in those cases where it comes from a place of genuine curiousity. 
a sexual assault/harrassment/rape is looked at differently in different places. and the victim's immediate family and the society she lives in plays a major role in how safe she feels in telling what happened. 
growing up my sister and i were raised by two fiercely protective parents. we could talk about anything under sun and our parents were ready to receive it. there was never a doubt in my head that if anything were to happen i would be given the necessary support from my family. but...that is a privilege that i am fortunate to have. not everyone is.
there are societies where the first response isn't 'i'm sorry! i'm here for you' or 'what can i do to help you?' but 'what did you do to get touched?' 'what did you do to get raped?'
case in point - harayana is a state in india where rape is widespread. last april, @thequint interviewed the locals in one of the villages there about the rape culture and here are some of their choicest words 'it takes two hands to clap.'
'once the girl reaches 14 years it's no longer considered as rape. it's consensual.'
'both the boy and the girl are at fault. but only the boy is held responsible and sent to jail and the girl is allowed to stay at home. the boy's life is ruined. that's not fair.'
'girls where jeans to attract boys and that is why they get raped.'
clearly these low, depraved ideas aren't confined only to india. it happens in the highest court of the most developed country to the darkest slums in the corners of the world.

tweet_full:
'why didn't she say anything?'
'why didn't she report?' i keep coming across these questions so many times that i really feel it needs to be addressed especially in those cases where it comes from a place of genuine curiousity. 
a sexual assault/harrassment/rape is looked at differently in different places. and the victim's immediate family and the society she lives in plays a major role in how safe she feels in telling what happened. 
growing up my sister and i were raised by two fiercely protective parents. we could talk about anything under sun and our parents were ready to receive it. there was never a doubt in my head that if anything were to happen i would be given the necessary support from my family. but...that is a privilege that i am fortunate to have. not everyone is.
there are societies where the first response is not 'i am sorry! i am here for you' or 'what can i do to help you?' but 'what did you do to get touched?' 'what did you do to get raped?'
case in point - harayana is a state in india where rape is widespread. last april, @thequint interviewed the locals in one of the villages there about the rape culture and here are some of their choicest words 'it takes two hands to clap.'
'once the girl reaches 14 years it is no longer considered as rape. it is consensual.'
'both the boy and the girl are at fault. but only the boy is held responsible and sent to jail and the girl is allowed to stay at home. the boy's life is ruined. that's not fair.'

repost by @belinda_vegan:  doomed to spend her entire life in a space so small, she's unable to even turn around.
pigs are among the smartest animals on earth. studies show that they are more #intelligent than #dogs and even some primates: they can play simple #videogames, teach each other and even learn names. they also form elaborate, cooperative social groups and feel #fear, pain and stress.

yet on farms, where pigs are kept in row after row after row of gestation crates throughout their pregnancies, they're also among the most abused. the 2-foot-wide cages are so narrow, the animals cannot even¬†turn around. they chew on the bars,¬†wave their heads incessantly back and forth,¬†or lie on the pavement in an apparent state of dejection. nearly immobilized, the pigs spend months staring ahead, waiting to be fed, likely going out of their minds. 
for a brief period while and after they give birth, they are placed in slightly larger farrowing crates, but they still can't turn around.¬†then their piglets are taken away and the sows are impregnated once more, returned to gestation crates to start the entire cycle of misery again.¬†
_
you don‚Äôt need to be a pig psychiatrist to see that the animals go insane in these crates. many develop obsessive behaviors indicating profound distress, such as endlessly waving their heads back and forth. others continuously bite the metal bars in front of them to the point that their gums and teeth are destroyed.
_
how would you feel about this being done to a dog or to a #cat? the only difference is your perception.

text:
everyone unable to accept the fact that someone they personally know or look up to has been accused via the #metoo movement,

it may be simple in folk tales and stories to see the hero defeat the villain. reality is a little more complex. you believe that people who harass are a different group, "the evil criminals" are not one of you. they're mentally ill psychopaths. 
news flash! this is not true.
humans are not intrinsically good or bad. we all have elements that may or may not be perceived as "good" dependent on various circumstances. 
people who have harassed someone are not necessarily always evil. they probably don't recognize harassment or it's impact on the victim. it's a pattern they follow and may not recognize what's wrong with it.

this one act of that person you like in that moment was wrong to the victim. i don't believe that everything about the perpetrator then is wrong. their art, contribution or friendship with you is separate but it is important for them to recognize where they went wrong.

i personally know perpetrators, people close to me who i still hangout with. i have seen and experienced their bad sides but they're still whole normal people outside of it.

a person needs to be called out by the victim so that they can reform their habbit. thank the one accusing someone important to you, they're helping the person get better.

also everyone saying "how can so many people be accused of harrasment? sab thodi aise karte hai?"
ask the women around you whether they ever have been groped, harrased, or faced any other form of sexual violation. you'll be shocked to know the number that hasn't is meagre
if so many people are being harassed, who's the one doing this to them.
maybe you and me unknowingly.
it's time we accept, apologise, learn and get better. 
#feminist #womenwriters #womensrights #sexualharassment
#feminisminindia #apologise 
#womenupliftingwomen #notallmen

text:
just said goodbye to these guys after a tour of @queensparkrangersfcoffcial and i have to say i‚Äôm pretty sad to see them all go.
.
it really sucks that so many others like them grow up in countries and communities where their gender means that they may be exploited, denied their human rights and even the essence of dignity without access to toilets and running water.
.
what i‚Äôve seen over the last ten days is that all these girls need is the opportunity to realise and demonstrate that they‚Äôre just like us; the lucky, privileged few.
.

text:
monday evening

i make myself a cup of tea
and sit down in the balcony enjoying the view
drinking my tea
humming my favorite song
'what a beautiful day' i say
suddenly i remember the horrific monday evening i spent with you
you took me out on a dinner
because i was new in town
i accepted the invitation
because my 'amma' knows you
and she said, "he is a good guy."
you knew i was scared of getting lost in the new town
so, after the dinner, you asked me, "should i drop you home?"
i said yes if you don't mind
when you dropped me, you asked me
if i could come and have a look at your place
i let you in
but you took that 'yes'
as a permission
for letting you inside my body
you came to my bedroom
and touched me
i cried for help
but you said 'it's okay it hurts.'
i shrieked and yelled
but you didn't move
you made me numb
every night i wept myself to bed
i felt foreign in my own body
i couldn't look myself in the mirror
for a year i slept in another room
i kept accusing myself
thought it was all my fault
but today on this beautiful monday evening
i enter my room
start making my bed
and keep my beloved cushions
i hang the beautiful paintings
and burn the scented candles
then i go to my bathroom and
put the music on
begin arranging flowers in the vase
i start loading my bathtub
i look at my reflection in the mirror and give a smile
that was full of acceptance¬†
i soak myself in the water
washing the bruises from that monday evening
i do not just clean my body
but i also purify my soul
and giving a tender hug to myself i say
"it's been such a long time since you were gone
but i am glad because finally, you're home." .
.
. .
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.  #writer#poet#poetry#poem#poetsofinstagram#writing#writingistherapy#writersporn#piemporn#writingprompts#writinginspiration#writersofinstagram#poetrycommunity#writerscommunity#indianwriters#poemsofinstagram#poetry_addicts#poetryslam#poertryishealing#whenheartcries#poetrygram#selflove#selfacceptance#metooinspired#finallyhome#justice#metoo

if i could come and have a look at your place
i let you in
but you took that 'yes'
as a permission
for letting you inside my body
you came to my bedroom
and touched me
i cried for help
but you said 'it is okay it hus.'
i shrieked and yelled
but you didn't move
you made me numb
every night i wept myself to bed
i felt foreign in my own body
i couldn't look myself in the mirror
for a year i slept in another room
i kept accusing myself
thought it was all my fault
but today on this beautiful monday evening
i enter my room
sta making my bed
and keep my beloved cushions
i hang the beautiful paintings
and burn the scented candles
then i go to my bathroom and
put the music on
begin arranging flowers in the vase
i sta loading my bathtub
i look at my reflection in the mirror and give a smile
that was full of acceptance¬†
i soak myself in the water
washing the bruises from that monday evening
i do not just clean my body
but i also purify my soul
and giving a tender hug to myself i say
"it is been such a long time since you were gone
but i am glad because finally, you are home." .
.
. .
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
every woman needs to read this!

the last few weeks has left me so fucking angry (#sorrynotsorry for the cussing). the news has been miserable and with the supreme court nomination still going through, i felt like i was being gaslighted by the whole country. i mean, basically, we all were. 
anyway, one of my favorite podcasters @cygf recommended this book and it contextualizes so much about what is going on in this world over the past few years. it goes in-depth into the #metoo movement, the 2016 election, anita hill 2nd wave feminism and so much more. 
it made me realize how much i have been suppressing my anger and now i'm forcing myself to listen to it so i know what i want to do with it. 
if you have been feeling angry too (i have had so many women friends tell me they are) then definitely pick up this book. 
also, use that anger to vote in the mid-term elections on november 6th!
.
.
.
.
.
.
#powerofanger #anger #rage #amreading #books #mustread #feminism #secondwavefeminism #fourthwavefeminism #readnow

in a society where independence is considered an invitation 
in a society where every other girl has a a #metoo story 
you are not a victim, but a survivor.

text:
#metoo

at last the guilt of holding truth was too much to bear
thanks to #metoo that gave us chance to roll our tears
this was our little secret which we kept in heart for years
it was a crime done by one who we thought to be venerable
in the end just turned out to be lascivious and lecherous
we live in times that make it all too easy for us
to become a case of what he said vs. what she said
why we still hear the cliched line ‚Äòmen will be men‚Äô
why powerful men like m j akbar and nana patekar get away 
with their crimes where victim herself becomes the culprit 
thanks to #metoo which took so long to come but good it came
it nonetheless told us that this akbar isn‚Äôt all that great
to all of you wonderful girls who cursed and cried in solitude
you are brave because you are not alone.....#metoo

text:
not #metoo

in the dark recess of my mind,  i felt my soul screaming metoo.
the difference was i couldn't recall the faces responsible for them.

over the years i have accumulated those unwanted gazes.
i have a memoirs of those gropings.
a book with stories of those eyes stripping me with stares.
eyes that were shorn of decency & humanity.
a million gestures that are filed when i travel.
if i speak aloud the sky would be filled with my cries of metoo.
i pledged to hit back when my little one felt the unwanted attention.
now i don't want to speak metoo.
because i hit backand scar those men for their very cowardice.
just so i don't have to say metoo.

#amwriting #lovewriting #poems #poemsporn #poet #word #wordgasm #writersofinstagram #writersnetwork #writings #igpoets #igwrite #poetrycommunity #writerscommunity #bhfyp - neeta arya

text:
hot news
salman khan bergabung dengan para daftar tokoh bollywood dengan pelaku pelecehan seksual üòØ

salman khan mendapat masalah, mantan kontributor acara yang dipandunya, bigg boss menuduh salman dan adiknya, aktor arbaaz khan telah melakukan kekerasan seksual.

salman khan, seorang sarjana bollywood yang menakjubkan telah terseret masuk ke dalam kontroversi gerakan #metoo yang sedang berlangsung baru-baru ini. setelah para bintang film dan sutradara-produser, yang datang terkuak satu demi satu dalam badai ini, sekarang salman khan telah bergabung dalam daftar.

mantan kontributor bigg boss ini menuduh salman khan dan keluarganya telah melakukan pelecehan seksual. pada sesi bigg boss 5, pooja mishra juga menuduh arbaaz khan bersama dengan shatrughan sinha, dan istrinya atas kasus pemerkosaan. dia mengklaim bahwa bukan hanya itu tetapi ayahnya diancam dibunuh oleh mereka.

menyusul dugaan big boss, mantan kontestan pooja mishra melawan salman khan dan shatrughan sinha, atas badai kontroversi besar ini dan dapat menjadi saksi di media sosial. pooja mishra juga mengungkapkan bahwa kedua anggota keluarga telah melecehkannya secara seksual selama syuting film sultan, film yang dibintangi salman khan. dia juga memposting serangkaian video yang menuduh salman khan dan yang lainnya di instagram.

namun, ini adalah salah satu berita mengejutkan karena salman khan yang terkenal karena kesederhanaannya dan untuk menghormati wanita di dalam dan di luar industri. salman khan dan keluarganya adalah keluarga terkenal dari industri film india. sementara aktor shatrughan sinha adalah seorang politisi terkenal dan bjp's bihar mp. 
tuduhan pada keluarga khan dan sinha benar-benar mengejutkan penggemar dan pengikut mereka. üòØ

text:
the #metoo movement is not about women v/s men. it is about the victim v/s the predator. it is about the society v/s the evil. i have some thoughts to share on it. please read on.
1. do not judge. if someone is opening up about it years later, it‚Äôs not necessary that he or she is lying. if you think you are strong enough to stand up for what is right at the time of the happening, great! try to empower others too. not everyone might be as strong as you are.
2. men who faced abuse, in any form, physical or verbal should open up about it. do not ridicule them and call them ‚Äògay‚Äô, ‚Äòeffeminate‚Äô, ‚Äòunmanly‚Äô in a condescending manner. 
3. there are some who might think that the #metoo movement will not bear any results. people will only talk and then the trend will die down. could be (even though harvey weinstein and the others were brought down). but if we stop trying, is there any point of living? it‚Äôs like saying we all have to die one day. we might as well not try too hard to live. if our ancestors had thought the same about all the movements they did, we wouldn't have got our independence.
4. if 2 or 3 or 4 women or men are complaining against the same person, who is not even a huge star (no point of getting any considerable benefit out of it), then there might be some truth to it. isn‚Äôt it? 
5. please be respectful when a person voices his/her story of abuse, even if it hasn‚Äôt yet been proven to be true. you might not have to agree with it. you can still be respectful. 
6. there are some who think that the women or the men had to stay quiet all these years to save their jobs, to protect their career. could be so. absolutely. after all, not everyone is as privileged to have well-to-do parents who have made their future secure. people fight and rebel to come to big cities and make a future. it‚Äôs not as easy to take it when they see their world crumble in front of them. (read the whole thing in the comment)

.
as women, may we live true to our authentic core of love. may we empower and support and respect one another as we each have our own personal ideas of what it means to be a woman. ‚ú®
.
as women, don‚Äôt ever forget we have the right to freedom and to equality and to our own individual voices (and have them heard). we have a right to be safe, to live in equanimity, a right for justice, to be acknowledged and loved‚Ä¶..yes, to be sweetly loved. üôè
.

.

text:
i have been seeing forwards and messages ridiculing the  #metoo movement. isn't this why, many women hesitate to speak about the harassments they have faced ? let us stop this !! all such posts, will not be entertained, in this community. 
why is the #metoomovement important ?

for a long time society has not addressed the issue of sexual harassment and assault. it was something left unspoken or seen as a private matter that was often left unacknowledged. the responsibility for the abuse was placed on the victim and not the perpetrator. many survivors of harassment and assault have felt the need to remain silent and were left to deal with their feels of shame and guilt privately. 
last but not the least, it's not a vindictive move to silence men - it is a movement that will highlight the need to respect sexual boundaries. and let us remember men are and have been victims of sexual harassment too !! it is for women and men alike

can it go overboard or misused?

at this point in time, i think we must be more concerned about it taking off in india. this can bring voices to many victims. they will know they are not alone and they don't have to deal with this privately. it will also send out a clear message to the sexual predators that this will not go away unnoticed and easily. 
how will this space/community support #metoo movement?

let us make a simple start. the one big reason why women don't come forward to report sexual crimes is because they are judged and commented upon. let us promise to keep this as a judgement free zone and not entertain any ridicule against the movement or the victims who speak up. ‚Äî with anshu bhatia and 2 others.
